type="user">jms-00ME</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00ME.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Enumerable set">Enumerable set</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is said to be <fr:em><fr:strong>enumerable</fr:strong></fr:em> whenever there exists a surjection <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A]]></fr:tex>, referred to as an <fr:em><fr:strong>enumeration</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:p>In an <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
title="Enumerable set"
addr="jms-00ME"
type="local">enumeration</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A]]></fr:tex> of a set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, we think of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> as a “code” for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> when <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}}=a]]></fr:tex>; these “codes” are not unique unless <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="jms-00KR.xml"
title="Bijection"
addr="jms-00KR"
type="local">bijection</fr:link>. By virtue of the viewpoint of quotients as surjections developed in <fr:link
href="jms-00MB.xml"
title="Quotients and surjections"
addr="jms-00MB"
type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-00MB" /></fr:link>, <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
title="Enumerable set"
addr="jms-00ME"
type="local">enumerability</fr:link> expresses when a given set can be built up from the natural numbers by quotienting (i.e. identifying codes that are taken to the same element by the <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
title="Enumerable set"
addr="jms-00ME"
type="local">enumeration</fr:link>).</fr:p><fr:tree
show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
title="Jon Sterling"
addr="jonmsterling"
type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
title="Marcelo Fiore"
addr="marcelofiore"
